The paper discusses inconsistency in pairwise comparisons, which is a common problem in decision-making and optimization. This topic is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), mathematical optimization (cs.MA), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper proposes inconsistency indicators and axiomatization, it is more likely to belong to cs.AI and cs.MA, which deal with decision-making and optimization.
